      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GETTING CHEEKY (2) hit the ground running from the squeeze draw with a slick early split, holding on for a minor placing when second and beaten 2.75 lengths at this track over 400m in 23.04. Makes plenty of appeal. FORGERY (1) has been close to a win, finishing in the minors three on end before a fourth when checked in the run last time in a Grade 6 at this track (31.51). May be worth another try. CERISE (4) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 2 lengths at Murray Bridge Straight in a handy 17.32 beating Lost Bearings. Awkwardly drawn but has the ability and in winning form. Should be in this for a long way. KILCOY LASS (5) was out of placings last time (23.32) at this track in a Grade 6, finishing sixth and beaten 6 lengths. Has already won two times from this draw.",
